cs.CE, cs.NA, cs.MS, cs.CG, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the application of IGA to engineering design scenarios and includes implementation aspects using Matlab. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper focuses on numerical methods for analysis and includes examples of linear elasticity and Poisson problems. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is a possible category as the paper includes a self-contained Matlab implementation. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of IGA in the context of T-spline geometries. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is an unlikely category as the paper does not discuss social or information networks.
